<p>This outlines how a moderator may lock whole topics or individual posts. There are various ways a moderator may do this, either by using the <a href="moderator_mcp.php" title="4.5. The Moderator Control Panel (MCP)">Moderator Control Panel</a> when viewing a forum, navigating to the selection menu beneath the topic in question, or editing any post within a topic and checking the relevant checkbox.</p><p>Locking a whole topic ensures that no user can reply to it, whereas locking individual posts denies the post author any editing permissions for that post.</p>